\value{
A list with class \code{mellio_payload}, structured according to
the v0.1 schema.
}
\description{
Converts a supported R model or test object into a structured JSON
payload (a "Result Card") that Mellio renders in the Stats section.
Pure and offline — no network calls. Use \code{\link[=mellio_open]{mellio_open()}} to additionally
open the payload in the Mellio web app.
}
\details{
Supported in v0: objects of class \code{htest} (\code{t.test}, \code{cor.test},
\code{wilcox.test}, \code{chisq.test}, \code{fisher.test}).

Schema: see \code{docs/STATS-R-BRIDGE-SCHEMA.md} in the repo. The payload
is value-only: numeric statistics, p-values, and CIs go through
unformatted; the Mellio web app applies citation-style rules
(decimals, italics, leading zeros).
}
\examples{
tt <- t.test(extra ~ group, data = sleep)
p <- mellio_payload(tt)
p$type
p$fields$statistic
}
